    g'(t) \amp =\amp  \displaystyle\frac{dy}{du} \cdot \frac{du}{dt}\\
    \amp \amp \\
    \amp =\amp  30 u^{4} (-3 \cos t - 2 \sin t) \\
    \amp =\amp  30 (-3 \sin t + 2 \cos t)^{4} (-3 \cos t - 2 \sin t) \\
  \end{array}

solution.p:
Aplicando a Regra da Cadeia duas vezes, obtemos:
\begin{array}{rcl} \frac{dy}{dx} \amp =\amp  10 (4 + \cos^2{x})^{9} \cdot \frac{d}{dx} (4 + \cos^2{x}) \quad \text{by the chain rule}\\
\amp =\amp  10 (4 + \cos^2{x})^{9} \cdot 2 \cdot \cos x \cdot \frac{d}{dx}( \cos x) 
\quad \text{by the chain rule}
\\ \amp =\amp  10 (4 + \cos^2{x})^{9} \cdot 2 \cdot \cos x \cdot ( -\sin x)
\\ \amp =\amp  -20 \cos x \sin x (4 + \cos^2{x})^{9}  
\end{array}
